DUBAI: Jordan’s King Abdullah II arrived in Abu Dhabi on a working visit on Thursday, Emirates News Agency reported.
The king was received on arrival by the president of the UAE Sheikh Mohamed bin Zayed Al-Nahyan. King Abdullah and Sheikh Mohamed discussed bilateral relations and ways of enhancing cooperation and joint action in various fields at the Qasr Al-Shati’ Palace. They also reviewed opportunities for developing collaboration in the fields of investment, development, and politics. King Abdullah’s accompanying delegation included Jordanian Prime Minister Dr. Bisher Al Khasawneh and the country’s Foreign Minister Ayman Safadi.